## Do NOT Touch (High Risk Areas)
- Payment Processing - Money, rounding, idempotency
- TSE Signature Chain - Fiscal compliance
- RKSV Special Receipts - Startbeleg, Monatsbeleg, Jahresbeleg, Schlussbeleg
- Decommissioned Register - No new sessions/payments
- Voucher Ledger - Balance integrity
- FinanzOnline Outbox - SOAP submission
- Tenant Isolation - Query filters, 404 semantics
- Singleton + EF Pattern - Always use `IServiceScopeFactory`

### RKSV DEP Â§7 Export Rules (Updated)

**Status:** â Implemented (F1âF5 complete)

- DEP export MUST include all RKSV Â§9 fields (5 tax rates, turnover counter)
- Signatures MUST be compact JWS with 3 parts (`header.payload.signature`)
- JWS payload MUST be RKSV Â§9 machine code (`_R1-AT1_âĶ`), not legacy JSON or QR payload
- DEP export MUST use `Belege-Gruppe` JSON structure with certificate grouping by thumbprint
- Certificate thumbprint MUST be stored in `payment_details.certificate_thumbprint` (and `DailyClosings.certificate_thumbprint` for Tagesabschluss)
- Certificate chain MUST be included (leaf + CA) per `Belege-Gruppe`
- Receipts MUST be ordered chronologically by `IssuedAt` then `SequenceNumber`
- Special receipts (Startbeleg, Monatsbeleg, Jahresbeleg, Schlussbeleg, Nullbeleg) MUST be included when `includeSpecialReceipts=true` (default `true`)
- Daily closings MUST be included when `includeDailyClosings=true` (default `true`)
- Permission `ReportExport` + `AuditView` required
- All DEP exports MUST be audited with `RksvDepExportJson` action
- API: `GET /api/admin/rksv/dep-export`
- PrÃžftool: `.\scripts\verify-rksv-dep-export.ps1 -DepExportPath "./dep-export.json" -CryptoMaterialPath "./crypto-material.json"`
- Guides: `docs/DEP_EXPORT_DEVELOPMENT.md`, `docs/DEP_EXPORT_COMPLETION.md`; canonical rules: `AGENTS.md`

## TSE Offline Mode
- Max **50** offline transactions per cash register
- When limit reached, POS must block new offline transactions
- Warning shown at 40 transactions (80% capacity)
- Offline queue persists across app restarts

## Session Security
- When username changes:
  1. Update `SecurityStamp`
  2. Invalidate all existing JWTs
  3. Force re-login on all devices
  4. Log the invalidation event

## Quick Reference

### Useful Commands
```bash
# Backend
dotnet run --project backend/KasseAPI_Final.csproj
dotnet ef migrations add <Name> --project backend
dotnet test

# FA
npm run dev
npm run generate:api
npm run test

# FE
npm start
npm run test
```

### Useful API Endpoints
```bash
# Health
curl http://localhost:5184/api/health

# Tenant switcher (dev)
curl -H "X-Tenant-Id: cafe" http://localhost:5184/api/tenants/switcher

# Login
curl -X POST http://localhost:5184/api/Auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"loginIdentifier":"admin","password":"***"}'

# Backup trigger
curl -X POST http://localhost:5184/api/admin/backup/trigger \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"
```

### Quick Reference (Backup)
```bash
# Trigger backup
curl -X POST http://localhost:5184/api/admin/backup/trigger \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"

# Check backup status
curl http://localhost:5184/api/admin/backup/status/latest \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"

# List backups
curl "http://localhost:5184/api/admin/backup/runs?page=1&pageSize=10" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"
```

### Quick Reference (Activity Feed)
```bash
# Get unread count
curl http://localhost:5184/api/admin/activities/unread-count \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"

# Mark as read
curl -X POST http://localhost:5184/api/admin/activities/{id}/read \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ***"
```

